steps.prompt:
You are a content strategist. Research the following topic and compile a structured brief for a blog post.

Topic: {{topic}}
Target SEO keyword: {{target_keyword}}
Target word count: {{word_count}}
Brand voice: {{brand_voice}}

Output a JSON object with fields: angle (the unique editorial angle, string), key_points (array of strings, 5-7 items), seo_keywords (array of strings, primary + secondary), competitor_gaps (array of strings, what competitors miss), suggested_title (string). Reply with only the JSON object.

You are a professional content writer. Write a complete blog post based on the research brief below.

Topic: {{topic}}
Target keyword: {{target_keyword}}
Word count: {{word_count}} words
Brand voice: {{brand_voice}}
Suggested title: {{steps.research-topic.output.suggested_title}}
Angle: {{steps.research-topic.output.angle}}
Key points: {{steps.research-topic.output.key_points}}
SEO keywords: {{steps.research-topic.output.seo_keywords}}

Write a complete, publication-ready post in Markdown. Include: H1 title, introduction, body sections with H2/H3, conclusion with CTA. Naturally incorporate SEO keywords. Match the brand voice exactly.

You are a social media copywriter. Based on the blog post below, write 3 social media post variants.

Blog title: {{steps.research-topic.output.suggested_title}}
Brand voice: {{brand_voice}}
Target keyword: {{target_keyword}}

Blog post:
{{steps.write-draft.output}}

Write 3 variants: (1) Twitter/X — punchy hook under 280 chars + link placeholder, (2) LinkedIn — professional 2-3 sentence teaser, (3) Instagram caption — engaging with relevant hashtags. Output a JSON object with fields: twitter, linkedin, instagram. Reply with only the JSON object.
